## These are all common dialogue entries that are shared across all of the
## courier quest kinds.
npc-response-quest-courier-start = I've marked your map to show you where to go.
npc-response-quest-courier-start_2 = If you can't find something, you can usually ask me or someone else for directions.
npc-response-quest-courier-start_3 =
    .a0 = Good luck on the journey.
    .a1 = Stay safe!
npc-response-quest-courier-where = I've updated the location on your map to show where { $name } is.
## For the "thank you" message, try to keep it as neutral as possible, because
## some quests may be happy or sad.
npc-response-quest-courier-thanks = Thank you for bringing this to me.
npc-response-quest-courier-generic-insufficient-items = Actually, it looks like you don't have all the required items. Come back when you've retrieved them.
dialogue-question-quest-courier-claim = I have something for you!
dialogue-question-quest-courier-where = Where can I find { $name }?
hud-map-spot-unspecified = No spot is required for this quest.

## Names of spots that could potentially require a visit.
spot-name-gnarling-totem = Gnarling Totem
spot-name-unspecified = spot

## This section is reserved for the different courier quests.
##
## First up are the courier quest items.
npc-response-quest-courier-ask = Can you deliver what is needed to { $name }, near { $site }? You'll be paid { $coins } coins upon delivery.
npc-response-quest-spot-courier-ask = Would you be able to bring { $name } near { $site } those items from the { $spot } as proof? You'll be paid { $coins } coins upon delivery.
dialogue-question-quest-courier-what = What am I getting for { $name } again?
dialogue-question-quest-courier-what-target = What am I getting for you again?

## Next up are the fetch quest items.
npc-response-quest-fetch-ask = Can you deliver what is needed to me? You'll be paid { $coins } coins upon delivery.
npc-response-quest-spot-fetch-ask = Would you be able to bring me what is needed from the { $spot } as proof? You'll be paid { $coins } coins upon delivery.
dialogue-question-quest-fetch-what = What am I getting for you again?

## Next up are the messenger quest items.
npc-response-quest-messenger-ask = Can you visit { $name } near { $site } and give them the message? I'll make sure that you get paid { $coins } coins for helping.
npc-response-quest-messenger-what-is-needed = You just need to find { $name } and talk to them - they'll get the message.
npc-response-quest-messenger-what-is-needed-target = Are you saying you have a message for me? What is it?
dialogue-question-quest-messenger-what = What am I telling { $name } again?
dialogue-question-quest-messenger-what-target = What am I telling you again?

## This section is reserved for the courier quest variants, such as Gnarling
## Carving, Legoom Leaf, Send Word, etc.
##
## First up are the Gnarling Carving items.
npc-response-quest-courier-gnarling-carving = There's a spot nearby where a bunch of gnarlings have gathered and built a totem. If you can eradicate some of them and bring proof in the form of a Gnarling Carving, you'll be rewarded.
npc-response-quest-courier-gnarling-carving-insufficient-items = It looks like you don't have at least one Gnarling Carving. Come back when you have one.
npc-response-quest-courier-gnarling-carving-what-is-needed = You need to get a Gnarling Carving, which can be taken from gnarlings by force, or from climbing up to the top of a gnarling totem.
hud-map-spot-gnarling-carving-label = Acquire a Gnarling Carving from a Gnarling Totem spot and return one to { $name }.

## Next up are the Legoom Leaf items.
npc-response-quest-courier-legoom-leaf = Legooms have been a minor pest in these parts, as of late... We need people to keep things under control. If you can eradicate some of them and bring proof in the form of a Legoom Leaf, you'll be rewarded.
npc-response-quest-courier-legoom-leaf-insufficient-items = It looks like you don't have at least one Legoom Leaf. Come back when you have one.
npc-response-quest-courier-legoom-leaf-what-is-needed = You need to get a Legoom Leaf, which can be taken from legooms by force. Legooms can be found all over the place.

## Next up is the Send Word messenger quest.
npc-response-quest-messenger-send-word = I need to send word to someone, but I don't have time to do it myself. I'll reward you if you can track them down and talk to them.

## Future courier quest variants will continue past here.
